Weema by Henrique Gog√≥ <henriquegogo@gmail.com>, 2020.

Window manager for minimalists

Installation:

  $ make
  $ sudo make install

Uninstall:
  
  $ sudo make uninstall

Usage:

  Edit .xinitrc file to 'exec weema' or select 'Weema'
  in your display manager.

Binds:

  Alt+Button1: raise and move window
  Alt+Tab: alternate windows
  Alt+F4: close window
  Ctrl+Alt+Delete: close window manager
  PrntScr: print screen
  Volume up: increase volume
  Volume down: decrease volume
  Super+R: open application launcher
  Super+T: open terminal
  Super+Shift+Up: maximize window
  Super+Shift+Down: move window to center and resize
  Super+Shift+Left: move window to left with full height
  Super+Shift+Right: move window to right with full height
  Super+Up: move window to top with half height
  Super+Down: move window to bottom with half height
  Super+Left: move window left and resize width
  Super+Right: move window right and resize width

Third party optional dependencies:
  
  Default weema-cmd script use some third party applications
  to manage some functions. You can edit weema-cmd and change
  them if you desire.

  - feh: set background image
  - dmenu: applications launcher
  - alsa-utils: volume control
  - scrot: print screen

